all apartment in mountain view california where they lived on welfare and used food stamps flickr  paul sableman in high school koum taught himself about computers by buying manuals from a local store and then returning each one when he finished reading it flickr  lauri rantalasource forbes although he was a selfconfessed troublemaker in high school who barely graduated koum enrolled at san jose state university and started working for ernst and young as a security tester associated presssources forbes linkedin one thing koum wishes he could erase from that part of his history is a restraining order from his exgirlfriend i feel i was irrational and behaved badly after we broke up koum said in  i am ashamed of the way i acted and ashamed that my behavior forced her to take legal action i am deeply sorry for what i did david ramossource bloomberg while on assignment for ernst and young in  koum met early yahoo employee brian acton six months later acton helped him get a security job there brian actonreuters while at yahoo koum joined an elite securityfocused hacker group called ww which included napsters shawn fanning and dozens of other members when a canadian teen launched a massive denialofservice attack on yahoo koum called on the crew for advice and help thomson reuterssource reuters koum remained at yahoo for nine years rising to become manager of infrastructure engineering but in  he and acton both left the company and spent some time traveling through south america ulysees padihla when they returned koum and acton applied to facebook ironically they were rejected facebook during their time off koum mulled over what he wanted to do next and came up with an idea for letting people set status updates on their phones koum incorporated whatsapp on his birthday february  in  by that summer he and acton decided to morph the product into a messaging app thewaybackmachine and so it began whatsapps first office was a couple of cubicles in the back of a converted warehouse shared by evernote where employees had to wrap blankets around themselves for warmth influenced by their time at yahoo acton and koum had a similar product philosophy advertising sucks sequoiasources forbes business insider koum and acton also cared deeply about user privacy from the getgo according to koum we want to know as little about our users as possible were not advertisementdriven so we dont need personal databases jan koumsource wired whatsapp quickly started growing organically without any marketing or pr especially in lesser developed countries that heavily relied on sms texting sequoia capital in  whatsapp caught the attention of facebook ceo mark zuckerberg who gave koum a call the two met for coffee and went on a hike scott olson  getty imagessourceÂ business insider koum and zuck stayed in touch going on more hikes and talking shop about connecting the world fastforward two years reuters in february  zuckerberg had koum over for dinner and put an acquisition offer on the table koum thought about it for a couple of days and then came back to zucks house on valentines day interrupting his dinner with wife priscilla they hashed out terms over chocolatecovered strawberries flickr  kathryn deckersource business insider the night before signing the final papers koum stayed up late going over everything with the team from the vc firm sequoia which had funded whatsapps series a driving home at  am koums tire blew out at  mph hour and he almost died shutterstocksource genius the next day in a somewhat symbolic move koum signed the paperwork for the facebook acquisition on the door of his former welfare office the office is just a few blocks away from whatsapps headquarters in mountain view facebookcomzuck suddenly as of february  koums stake in whatsapp was worth  billion his net worth would continue to surge along with facebooks stock value david ramos  getty imagessource forbes koum joined facebooks board and agreed to a yearly base salary of  with stock options worth billions he would continue to lead whatsapp out of a nondescript office in mountain view miles away from facebooks headquarters mark zuckerberg facebooks business development chief amin zoufonoun and koumfacebookcomzucksource the wall street journal the whatsapp team celebrated the facebook deal by popping bottles of cristal champagne igor solomennikov one of whatsapps first employees posted this photo to instagram though he later took it down a bottle of cristal typically costs about  instagram via sgoshsource business insider just days after the acquisition was announced koum and whatsapp cofounder brian acton jetted off to barcelona for the mobile world congress they took some time there to party koum celebrated the acquisition and his th birthday with a massive paparazzifilled party at a nightclub called boujis boujis barcelona tumblrsources daily mail tumblr but even though hes now worth billions koum has carried his moneysaving ways into adulthood he pressured facebook to close the deal in time for his flight to barcelona which he couldnt change and had bought with frequentflier miles dinuka liyanawattereuterssource gizmodo just months after whatsapp was bought koum made a serious turn to philanthropy quietly making a  million donation to the silicon valley community foundation apsource sfgate he also donated  million to the foundation responsible for the opensource operating system freebsd in a way freebsd helped lift me out of poverty koum wrote at the time one of the main reasons i got a job at yahoo is because they were using freebsd and it was my operating system of choice freebsdsource facebook despite his wealth koum has maintained a low profile throughout his career he claims that selling whatsapp to facebook only changed  of his life and that he still lives in the same house and has the same friends reuterssource medium one of koums few indulgences is his love for porsches â€œfor me a porsche always represented the epitome of success he said in  and the desire to have a car like that was a key incentive to learn more and to work even harderâ€ shutterstocksource porsche koum has been selling his facebook shares at a rapid pace he unloaded more than half of his holdings in  alone totaling roughly  billion for comparison mark zuckerberg sold roughly  billion in stock last year facebook when facebook bought whatsapp for a stunning  billion in  the app had about  million monthly active users today it has  billion reuters for now koum seems focused on growing whatsapp around the world the apps largest market is india at this moment i am busy working on whatsapp and i keep thinking all the time how i can make this product better he said last year associated pressaijaz rahi source medium jillian donfro contributed to an earlier version of this story see also the fabulous life of snap ceo evan spiegel one of the youngest billionaires in the world more whatsapp billionaires jan koum facebook mark zuckerberg features facebook linkedin twitter email print Ã— recommended for you powered by sailthru the ragstoriches story of whatsapp cofounder jan koum who grew up without running water and is now worth over  billion the ragstoriches story of whatsapp cofounder jan koum who grew up without running water and is now worth over  billion few people haveÂ benefited from facebooks recommended for you disclaimer featured apple is lagging the market as iphone  woes mount more the bottom lineÂ Â» heres how much you need to save for college every year depending on when you start more year by yearÂ Â» tech insider emails  alerts get the best of business insider delivered to your inbox every day signup get the slide deck from henry blodgets ignition presentation on the future of digital Â  Â  read business insider on the go available on ios or android find a job tech jobs clevel jobs media jobs design jobs finance jobs sales jobs see all jobs Â» thanks to our partners follow us on also check out  copyright   business insider