nterest youtube snapchat celebrity things to know about jan koum founder of the  billion whatsapp by melissa lockerposted on february   at am edt sharetweetemail pinterest ap whatâ€™s whatsapp that was the question on everyoneâ€™s lips when facebook announced earlier this week that it would pay at least  billion for the text messaging application which has  million users around the world the app does not sell advertising and has very little revenue but offers facebook even more access to the fastgrowing world of instant messaging the company was founded by jan koum  who was relatively unknown outside of silicon valley circles until facebook came calling the lowkey ceo gave very few media interviews as his messaging service quietly grew on the grounds that press distracts from the actual product now that the product has sold for a staggering sum all eyes are on the newly anointed hotshot ceo here are seven things to know about the newest tech titan  he was born and raised in a small village outside of kiev ukraine according to a profile in forbes he is the only child of a housewife and a construction manager and grew up in a house with no hot water at  he and his mother immigrated to silicon valley where they struggled financially and lived on food stamps his father died in  his mother in   as a teenager koum taught himself computer programming he did it by purchasing used books and returning them to the store when he was done with them he enrolled in san jose state university but dropped out when he got a job at yahoo as an infrastructure engineer  he signed his deal with facebook at the north county social services office he used to collect food stamps there with his mother emotional moment jan signs whatsappfacebook paperwork at welfare office where he got his food stamps as a teen pictwittercomijliswxi â€” jim goetz jimgoetz february    in  koum wanted to give up he wanted to pack whatsapp in but his friend and eventual cofounder brian acton talked him out of it by early  whatsapp was in the top  of all apps in the us itunes app store by february  whatsapp had almost  million active users  mark zuckerberg had to court him the facebook ceo had his eye on whatsapp for a long time and began wooing koum early in  their long courtship included quiet dinners long walks and coffee shop conversations  koum reportedly sealed the deal with facebook over chocolatecovered strawberries they were originally intended for zuckerbergâ€™s wife priscilla chan but koum got them instead  his net worth is now around  billion forbes estimates that koum owns approximately  percent of whatsapp which translates to him netting about  billion in the deal like us on facebook for more stories like this show full article most popular  kourtney kardashian reveals the caffeinated drink she swears by â€˜it makes my tummyÂ flatterâ€™  super exhausted why justin bieber canceled his purpose world tour  save the date check out joseph duggar  kendra caldwells romantic engagement photos  luke bryan finally breaks his no butttouching rule for yearold terminally illÂ fan  life imitates art are riverdales cole sprouse  lili reinhart dating see also send to email address your name your email address cancel post was not sent  check your email addresses email check failed please try again sorry your blog cannot share posts by email jan koum  wikipedia jan koum from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search jan koum jan koum left with brian acton nativeÂ name ÑĞ½ ĞºÑƒĞ¼ born  february   ageÂ  kiev ukrainian ssr soviet union citizenship american almaÂ mater san jose state university dropped out occupation ceo of whatsapp  managing director in facebook inc yearsÂ active   present organization whatsapp inc knownÂ for cofounded whatsapp homeÂ town fastiv ukraine netÂ worth us billion may  jan koum ukrainian ÑĞ½ ĞºÑƒĞ¼ born february   is an american internet inventor and computer programmer he is the ceo and cofounder of whatsapp with brian acton a mobile messaging application which was acquired by facebook inc in february  for us billion in  he entered the forbes list of the  richest americans at position  with an estimated worth of more than seven and half billion dollars he was the highestranked newcomer to the list that year contents  life and career  trivia  references  external links life and careeredit koum was born in kiev ukraine then part of the soviet union he is of jewish origin he grew up in fastiv outside kiev and moved with his mother and grandmother to mountain view california in  where a social support program helped the family to get a small twobedroom apartment at the age of  his father had intended to join the family later but finally remained in ukraine at first koums mother worked as a babysitter while he himself worked as a cleaner at a grocery by the age of  he became interested in programming he enrolled at san jose state university and simultaneously worked at ernst  young as a security tester in february  a restraining order was granted against koum in state court in san jose california an exgirlfriend detailed incidents in which she said koum verbally and physically threatened her in october  koum said about the restraining order i am ashamed of the way i acted and ashamed that my behavior forced her to take legal action in  jan koum was hired by yahoo as an infrastructure engineer shortly after he met brian acton while working at ernst  young as a security tester over the next nine years they worked at yahoo in september  koum and acton left yahoo and took a year off traveling around south america and playing ultimate frisbee both applied and failed to work at facebook in january  he bought an iphone and realized that the thensevenmonthold app store was about to spawn a whole new industry of apps he visited his friend alex fishman and the two talked for hours about koums idea for an app over tea at fishmans kitchen counter koum almost immediately chose the name whatsapp because it sounded like whats up and a week later on his birthday february   he incorporated whatsapp inc in california whatsapp became popular in just a short amount of time and this caught facebooks attention facebooks founder mark zuckerberg first contacted koum in the spring  the two began meeting at a coffee shop in los altos california then began a series of dinners and walks in the hills above silicon valley  on february   zuckerberg asked koum to have dinner at his home and formally proposed koum a deal to join the facebook board   days later facebook announced it was acquiring whatsapp for us billion usd over the first half of  koum sold more than  billion worth of facebook stock which was about a half of his total holdings he is estimated to still own another  billion in facebook stock his mother died in  of cancer in the united states while his father died in ukraine in  triviaedit jan koum was part of a group of hackers called ww where he met the future founders of napster shawn fanning and jordan ritter in november  koum donated one million dollars to the freebsd foundation and close to  million to the silicon valley community foundation svcf the same year referencesedit  httpwwwforbescomprofilejankoum  why whatsapps founder hates being called an entrepreneur retrieved Â   forbes announces its rd annual forbes  ranking of the richest americans  september  forbescom accessed  november   whatsapp founder jan koums jewish ragstoriches tale the jewish daily forward reuters  february  retrieved  march Â   rowan david whatsapp the inside story wired uk wiredcouk retrieved Â   a b c d e f parmy olson february   exclusive the ragstoriches tale of how jan koum built whatsapp into facebooks new  billion baby forbes retrieved february  Â   whatsapp jan koum â€“ the story of a man who kept it simple jewish business news feb th   de jong david  facebooks jan koum apologizes for past restraining order bloombergÂ   the memories from ragstoriches by jan koum eyerys retrieved may  Â   olson