running around in circles jan koum good vision end communication is at the very core of our society thats what makes us human jan koum communication society core marketing and press kicks up dust it gets in your eye and then youre not focusing on the product jan koum eye marketing you i didnt have a computer until i was   but i did have an abacus jan koum computer until did i grew up in a society where everything you did was eavesdropped on recorded snitched on i had friends when we were kids getting into trouble for telling anecdotes about communist leaders jan koum friends society you i grew up in a country where i remember my parents not being able to have a conversation on the phone the walls had ears and you couldnt speak freely jan koum parents remember speak when i was a kid trying to communicate with family in the soviet union it was very difficult you had to go through the longdistance phone companies like mci which were difficult to navigate and expensive to make calls through jan koum family trying you anybody can build a company and sell the company the next day that doesnt make you special it doesnt make you unique it doesnt make you all that great jan koum great day unique at whatsapp our engineers spend all their time fixing bugs adding new features and ironing out all the little intricacies in our task of bringing rich affordable reliable messaging to every phone in the world thats our product and thats our passion your data isnt even in the picture we are simply not interested in any of it jan koum time passion world people have sms right it stinks its a dead technology like a fax machine left over from the seventies sitting there as a cash cow for carriers jan koum technology people cow nobody should have the right to eavesdrop or you become a totalitarian state  the kind of state i escaped as a kid to come to this country where you have democracy and freedom of speech jan koum freedom democracy you experiences from our youth shape what we do later in life jan koum life youth experiences people appreciate a good product a stable system they want to communicate easily and use a product that just works jan koum good appreciate people i had so much fun in early days learning about networking security scalability and other geeky stuff jan koum learning fun networking on my iphone gs i use instagram twitter and touch jan koum iphone touch twitter in some ways you can think of endtoend encryption as honoring what the past looked like jan koum past think you we hear lots of stories where grandparents go to a store and buy a smartphone so they can keep in touch with kids and grandkids jan koum touch grandparents go we want to do one thing and do it really well for us thats communications between people who are friends and relatives jan koum friends people want the fword here is focus jan koum focus here the encryption genie is out of the bottle jan koum bottle genie out we dont really talk about our future plans but we at the same time try to build things that our users ask us for jan koum time future build in some countries whatsapp is like oxygen jan koum oxygen like countries a lot of what i experienced growing up in the ussr and coming to the us as an immigrant actually reflects itself in whatsapp experiences from our youth shape what we do later in life jan koum life youth growing up were not interested in bombarding our users with hey play this game play this game play this game it gets annoying it gets in the way of messaging and it gets in the way of staying in touch with people who are important to you jan koum game people play i only have one idea that is whatsapp and i am going to continue to focus on that i have no plans to build any other ideas jan koum focus i am ideas i grew up in russia we had a telephone line but a load of our neighbours didnt it became a shared resource for the whole apartment complex people would come and knock on the door and ask to call their family in another city jan koum family door city share this page cite this page citation find on amazon jan koum related authors steve jobs warren buffett henry ford bill gates jim rohn stephen covey peter drucker les brown brainyquote desktop brainyquote mobile site home authors topics quote of the day pictures top  quotes professions birthdays social bq on facebook bq on twitter bq on pinterest bq on google bq on instagram shop brainyquote store apps iphoneipad app quote of the day feeds javascript and rss feeds wordpress plugin quote of the day email about about us contact us submit privacy terms copyright     brainyquote Â  loading load more quotes forbes welcomeclose more options quote of the day learning never exhausts the mind leonardo da vinci timeline of whatsapp  wikipedia timeline of whatsapp from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search the following is a timeline of whatsapp a proprietary crossplatform encrypted instant messaging client for smartphones full timelineedit year month and date event type details  february  company jan koum incorporates whatsapp in california  october funding brian acton persuades five exyahoo friends to invest  in seed funding and is granted cofounder status  august product whatsapp  is released on the app store for the iphone  december product whatsapp for the iphone is updated to send photos  august product whatsapp support for android os is added  january  competition wechat a messenger app is founded it eventually becomes very popular in china  april funding in series a round whatsapp founders agree to take  million from sequoia capital on top of their  seed funding after months of negotiation with sequoia partner jim goetz  may competition snapchat a competing photo messaging app is founded  january  security an unknown hacker publishes a website that makes it possible to change the status of an arbitrary whatsapp user as long as the phone number was known  august security the whatsapp support staff announce that messages were encrypted in the latest version of the whatsapp software for ios and android but not blackberry windows phone and symbian without specifying the cryptographic method  february userbase whatsapps user base swells to about  million active users and its staff to   july funding sequoia invests another  million in series b round valuing whatsapp at  billion  july  product whatsapp goes free with an annual subscription fee of  after the first year  august competition telegram a cloudbased instant messaging service launches  august product whatsapp introduces voice messaging  february  company facebook announces its acquisition of whatsapp for us billion its largest acquisition to date facebook pays  billion in cash  billion in facebook shares and an additional  billion in restricted stock units granted to whatsapps founders  march security someone discovers a vulnerability in whatsapp encryption on the android application that allows another app to access and read all of a userâ€™s chat conversations within it  november product whatsapp introduces a feature named read receipts which alerts senders when their messages are read by recipients within a week whatsapp introduces an update allowing users to disable this feature so that message recipients do not send acknowledgements  january  product whatsapp launches whatsapp web a web client which can be used through a web browser by syncing with the mobile devices connection  january  product whatsapp announces its policy on cracking down on rdparty clients including whatsapp users would not be able to use whatsappâ€™s services at all until the thirdparty apps are uninstalled  december legal whatsapp is briefly shut down in brazil after it refuses to place wiretaps on certain whatsapp accounts it is shut down in brazil again on may  and in july   january  product jan koum announces that whatsapp will no longer charge its users a  annual subscription fee there is still no clear plan for monetizing whatsapp  march legal diego dzodan a facebook executive is arrested by brazilian federal police after facebook fails to turn over information from his whatsapp messaging account into a judges request for a drug trafficking investigation  march  product whatsapp introduces its documentsharing feature initially allowing users to share pdf files with their contacts  april  product security whatsapp and open whisper systems announce that they finish adding endtoend encryption  to every form of communication on whatsapp and that users could now verify each others keys  may  product whatsapp is introduced for both windows and mac operating systems referencesedit  metz cade  april  forget apple vs the fbi whatsapp just switched on encryption for a billion people wired magazine condÃ© nast retrieved  may Â   a b c d e parmy olsen february   exclusive the ragstoriches tale of how jan koum built whatsapp into facebooks new  billion baby forbes retrieved january  Â   whatsapp  is submitted  whatsapp blog retrieved june  Â   threequarters of whatsapp users are on android  on ios study venturebeatcom retrieved june  Â    years of wechat retrieved june  Â   snapchat retrieved june  Â   schellevis joost january   whatâ€™s app status van anderen os nog steeds te wÄ³zigen in dutch tweakers retrieved january  Â   rvdm january   how whatâ€™s app net works wire trip retrieved april  Â   are my messages secure whatsapp faq zendesk august   retrieved january  Â   privco privcocom retrieved may  Â   the granddaddy of messaging apps whatsapp finally goes for a subscription model on ios techcrunchcom retrieved june  Â   whatsapp the internet messenger to become free the new york times retrieved august  Â   russias zuckerberg launches telegram a new instant messenger service reuterscom retrieved june  Â   voice messaging comes to whatsapp techcrunchcom retrieved june  Â   whatsapp was valued at b in final round before sale techcrunch retrieved february  Â   facebook to buy whatsapp for  billion the wall street journal retrieved au