loading a lot of times people start out with a lot of good ideas but then they dont execute they lose the purity of their vision you end up running around in circles jan koum good vision end communication is at the very core of our society thats what makes us human jan koum communication society core marketing and press kicks up dust it gets in your eye and then youre not focusing on the product jan koum eye marketing you i didnt have a computer until i was   but i did have an abacus jan koum computer until did i grew up in a society where everything you did was eavesdropped on recorded snitched on i had friends when we were kids getting into trouble for telling anecdotes about communist leaders jan koum friends society you i grew up in a country where i remember my parents not being able to have a conversation on the phone the walls had ears and you couldnt speak freely jan koum parents remember speak when i was a kid trying to communicate with family in the soviet union it was very difficult you had to go through the longdistance phone companies like mci which were difficult to navigate and expensive to make calls through jan koum family trying you anybody can build a company and sell the company the next day that doesnt make you special it doesnt make you unique it doesnt make you all that great jan koum great day unique at whatsapp our engineers spend all their time fixing bugs adding new features and ironing out all the little intricacies in our task of bringing rich affordable reliable messaging to every phone in the world thats our product and thats our passion your data isnt even in the picture we are simply not interested in any of it jan koum time passion world people have sms right it stinks its a dead technology like a fax machine left over from the seventies sitting there as a cash cow for carriers jan koum technology people cow nobody should have the right to eavesdrop or you become a totalitarian state  the kind of state i escaped as a kid to come to this country where you have democracy and freedom of speech jan koum freedom democracy you experiences from our youth shape what we do later in life jan koum life youth experiences people appreciate a good product a stable system they want to communicate easily and use a product that just works jan koum good appreciate people i had so much fun in early days learning about networking security scalability and other geeky stuff jan koum learning fun networking on my iphone gs i use instagram twitter and touch jan koum iphone touch twitter in some ways you can think of endtoend encryption as honoring what the past looked like jan koum past think you we hear lots of stories where grandparents go to a store and buy a smartphone so they can keep in touch with kids and grandkids jan koum touch grandparents go we want to do one thing and do it really well for us thats communications between people who are friends and relatives jan koum friends people want the fword here is focus jan koum focus here the encryption genie is out of the bottle jan koum bottle genie out we dont really talk about our future plans but we at the same time try to build things that our users ask us for jan koum time future build in some countries whatsapp is like oxygen jan koum oxygen like countries a lot of what i experienced growing up in the ussr and coming to the us as an immigrant actually reflects itself in whatsapp experiences from our youth shape what we do later in life jan koum life youth growing up were not interested in bombarding our users with hey play this game play this game play this game it gets annoying it gets in the way of messaging and it gets in the way of staying in touch with people who are important to you jan koum game people play i only have one idea that is whatsapp and i am going to continue to focus on that i have no plans to build any other ideas jan koum focus i am ideas i grew up in russia we had a telephone line but a load of our neighbours didnt it became a shared 